              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The sample materials were electrodeposited on 36 mm",
                " diameter by 0.3 or 0.4 mm thick platinum plates.",
                "The diameter of deposition was 25 mm.",
                "Isotopic composition and number of atoms were",
                " determined by measuring the alpha spectrum and",
                " activity.",
                "Details of the samples are given in Table 1 of NETU-47.",
                "During irradiations, the samples were placed",
                " perpendicular to the beam at a distance of 5 to 10 cm",
                " from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross section ratios were corrected for events",
                " caused by room-scattered neutrons.",
                "Corrections due to the pulse-height discrimination",
                " were made by extrapolating to zero pulse-height,",
                " using a Gaussian function.",
                "Corrections were also applied for self-absorption of",
                " fission fragments in the samples, as well as for",
                " fission induced by low energy neutrons.",
                "Contributions from impurities in the samples,",
                " especially the spontaneous fission of Cm-244 present",
                " in the Am-243 sample, were also corrected for."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
